Summary

In this doc, we compare all of the hydrophobicity scales on this site.

There is a wide range of distributions for the different scales. Some are bimodal, some are unimodal, some are skewed, some are symmetrical. Lets look at each distribution individually with their mixture models, intersections, and colour verified SRP independent proteins.

The split looks very good for both the yes and no populations, now it’s time to calculate the errors for both Kyte Doolittle and Rose.

## number of iterations= 13
## number of iterations= 197

## [1] "Rose error: 0.0582010582010582"
## [1] "KD error: 0.037037037037037"
## [1] "Rose false positive: 0.024390243902439 Rose false negative: 0.0841121495327103"
## [1] "KD false positive: 0.0365853658536585 KD false negative: 0.0373831775700935"

The errors are very similar for both scales, but Rose has a lower false positive and higher false negative rate. You can see the small cluster of SRP proteins that are at the bottom of the left mode.
